### 6. Validation Best Practices

#### Fail Fast Principle
- Validate at the earliest possible point
- Return errors immediately to avoid wasted processing
- Provide clear, actionable error messages

#### Graceful Degradation
- Continue processing when individual records fail
- Track failures and report in response
- Don't fail entire batch for single record issues

#### Comprehensive Feedback
- Include all validation errors in response
- Provide specific error codes for each validation type
- Include context (e.g., which institutions not found)

